  "texts": [
    "Validating our measure using standard holdout samples, we achieve an average AUROC of 0.82, with a range of 0.80 to 0.84.",
    "3 To further test the measure, we conduct two additional validation exercises.",
    "In the first, we analyze commercial outcomes, such as patent citations and renewals, for over 5.2 million academic papers from US-based research universities.",
    "The results strongly confirm the predictive power of our measure: articles with high commercial potential, as identified by our model, are significantly more likely to be commercialized, evidenced by their citation in renewed patents.",
    "For instance, an article in the top quartile of our measure is more than 20 times more likely to be cited by a renewed patent than an article in the bottom quartile."
